messages.text: The next day, Jenna gets a text from Heather.
Still stuck in this meeting! Think I can make it to happy hour in 30.
I already got both of us wine. The merlots and I will be waiting.
You’re there early. Didn’t you go to your place from the airport first?
Or are you afraid Adam hasn’t left yet?
Jenna glances at the small suitcase stowed near her legs under the bar.
I thought I would get here before the crowd.
Snagged us seats in a corner where not even the bartender will bother us.
It has nothing to do with Adam.
Whatever you say.
With a long sigh, Jenna leans an elbow on the bar.
Someone tall and broad slides onto the barstool next to her.
She doesn’t even have the energy to look at him.
Sorry, that seat’s—
A low male voice buzzes over her neck.
Last night you said you didn’t want to face me after what we’d started.
So keep those eyes down, Rosy.
Oh God.
Just look at your phone.
What the hell are you doing, Adam?
Leaving you a parting gift before my trip.
I know you and Heather have happy hour here every Wednesday when you’re in town.
So I took a chance to see you.
I—
Since you've been enjoying our texts so much, I thought we’d try something new.
Just think of this as a very intense conversation.
He slides his big hand over her thigh.
She sucks in a harsh breath.
That’s right. Give that little monster inside permission to enjoy this.
I’m not sure this is a good—
Idea? Then stop thinking.
Okay. I’m…I’m ready.
He slowly pulls up her business skirt.
Impulsively, she parts her legs, then bites down hard on her lip.
Someone’s going to see.
See what?
We’re in a corner. The bar is blocking what’s happening below the surface.
He traces his fingertips between her thighs.
Electricity zings through her, then pounds through her blood.
This is…
Better than a text?
Mmm…
Agreed, because now I can see the blood rushing to your face, making you blush.
I can imagine how this moment is making you feel.
Her pulse jerks in response to the featherlike strokes up her thigh.
He’s getting closer…
Closer…
Do you know how many times I wanted to do this to you at the library in college?
You’d be wearing one of your cute skirts with manga knee socks and UGG boots.
I couldn’t keep my damned mind on those numbers for calculus…
I was too busy thinking about breaking YOU down.
She opens her legs a little more.
Something inside her is aching…
If you’re looking to break me down…
God, you’re doing a good job of it.
Jesus, your skin is as soft as I thought it’d be.
He traces his fingertips higher, then pauses.
The phone screen blurs in Jenna’s line of sight as she bites her lip harder.
He brushes a fingertip against the center of her.
Oh!
Adam laughs under his breath.
You had a lot of lace in your bedroom drawers.
All I’ve been thinking about is you in those pretty things.
But it’s not lace that I want to feel.
Adam…
What would happen if I slip my finger under your panties like…
He slides beneath the lace edge, stroking her.
Jenna lowers her head, totally high on heat and adrenaline.
…this?
Mmhm…
Don’t clutch the bar, Rosy. It’s a dead giveaway.
She trembles, the pressure building.
Now I’m never going to be able to face you.
We’ll see about that.
I’m still going to try and change your mind.
You won’t.
Why the hell not?
His whisper is rough, impatient.
He feels so good inside her that she turns her face all the way to the other side.
Ohmygod.
It’s all she can do not to move with every pump.
It’s all she can do to feel the steam pulsing in her, gathering…
Almost there…almost…
A quiet, intense orgasm rocks her. She grips his muscled thigh and shudders.
There she is. The woman I was looking for…
He removes his hand and straightens her skirt, then presses his mouth to her ear.
I’ve got a plane to catch to LA so I can start moving into my house and the new office.
I won’t be back for a few days to grab the last of my stuff.
That gives you some time to think about us, Rosy.
Think hard. I really hope you change your mind.
He leaves as discreetly as he came.
It takes Jenna fifteen minutes before she can try to pull herself back together.
When she has all her things, she texts Heather.
I’m already on the subway home. Rain check for another happy hour?
How about tomorrow? Maybe I’ll be out of this meeting by then.
Yeah, and maybe my brain will sort out what just happened.
Something happened?
Adam came into the bar and…
I don’t even know what to call it.
It was…intense. Then he left.
But before he did, he told me that I need to think about us being together.
What?!
I’m not sure whether I should be turned on or utterly despaired…
Because I don’t know if I have the guts to be with him that way.
I mean, then he’d see all of me, right?
Jenna…
We’ve never touched like that.
And, God, it was so, so good.
I’m totally gonna ask for details later. All I want to know right now is…
Will you change your mind about letting him in?
Jenna leans back in her subway seat, not knowing how to answer that.
